{"questionId":"13924733","questionHtml":"<p>Show, using calculus, that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi></math> is a decreasing function of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>p</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;or equivalent (e.g. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>'</mo></math>)&nbsp;and <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>p</mi></mfrac></math>.&nbsp;Do not accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;for the first <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>unless followed by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math>,&nbsp;which can earn <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>(for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>1</mn></math>) we therefore have&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>I</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>p</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence the function is decreasing&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13924733","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.2aii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show, using calculus, that I is a decreasing function of p.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.2—Increasing and decreasing functions","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.9—Differentiating standard functions and derivative rules","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.9—HL modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}